                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_byru" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>byru</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>buru</orth><form type="variant"><orth>buræw</orth></form></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ограждение</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>enclosure</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ограда</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>fence</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>крепостная стена</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>town wall</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>вал</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>wall</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ров</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>ditch</q></tr></sense></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>byrū kʼærtgængæjæ ū</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ограду надо проломить</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the fence must be broken</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>124</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>xucawæn iskuvta, sæ astæw ustur buræw kud festadajdæ obæl</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>он взмолился богу, чтобы между ними образовался большой ров</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>he prayed to god to form a big ditch between them</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 59</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>byrū kʼærtgængæjæ ū</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ограду надо проломить</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the fence must be broken</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>124</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>xucawæn iskuvta, sæ astæw ustur buræw kud festadajdæ obæl</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>он взмолился богу, чтобы между ними образовался большой ров</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>he prayed to god to form a big ditch between them</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 59</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>buru</w> <gloss><q>крепость</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/> <w>buru</w> <gloss><q>ограда</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/> <w>baru</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="aqc"><lang/> <w>baru</w></mentioned> и в других дагестанских языках; сюда же <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>bera</w> <gloss><q>предел</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/> <gloss><q>граница</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Чубинов"/></bibl>), ‘огороженное место, где доят овец’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Чкония"/></bibl>). Все перечисленные слова ведут к <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>bārū</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w>bāra</w> <gloss><q>крепостная стена</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/> <gloss><q>вал</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/> <gloss><q>ограда</q></gloss></mentioned>, , восходящему к <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>vāra-</w> <gloss><q>ограждение</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._PSt."/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>).</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Cf. <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>buru</w> <gloss><q>fortress</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/> <w>buru</w> <gloss><q>fence</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/> <w>baru</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="aqc"><lang/> <w>baru</w></mentioned> and in other Dagestan languages; also here <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>bera</w> <gloss><q>limit</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/> <gloss><q>border</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Чубинов"/></bibl>), ‘enclosed place where sheep are milked’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Чкония"/></bibl>). All listed words lead to <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>bārū</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w>bāra</w> <gloss><q>town wall</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/> <gloss><q>wall</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/> <gloss><q>fence</q></gloss></mentioned>,  which traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>vāra-</w> <gloss><q>enclosure</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._PSt."/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>).</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>